content.description: Start on a good hold left of the arete, find something to put your feet on, and make your way up and right to a slopey top out. Best done as a dyno to the lip.
content.location: On the Noodle boulder, between Victor and Corner Direct

content.description: Sit start both hands on v shaped crimp on the left face. Make a big move with poor feet up to another crimp then to the top.
content.location: Far left side on the left face of the Noodle Boulder.

content.description: Sit start with both hands on the jug and head up and to the right using any hands on the right face and the arete.
content.location: On the Noodle Boulder, both hands on the chalked jug. Same start as corner direct and Shmoil to Woody.

content.description: sit start on obvious chalked up jug on arete (same as corner direct). then work out left using a terrible intermediate if needed (decent feet make it possible). eventually make the span left to the good incut hold on the face (the face facing the river, it's a unique hold, some kind of quartzite maybe). from here head straight up using a "sharks tooth" like hold if needed.
content.protection: pads and spotter. relatively flat and obstruction free landing.
content.location: From the cave boulder walk downhill towards the river. The noodle boulder main face faces the river.

content.description: I don't like quoting the guidebooks but there's really no other good explanation. sit start on obvious chalked up jug. then work the crimps on either side of the arete up to a sloped top out. left hand finger strength is a must as the 2 left hand crimps are pretty hideous.
content.protection: pads and spotter. relatively flat and obstruction free landing.
content.location: From the cave boulder walk downhill towards the river. The noodle boulder main face faces the river.

content.description: The first boulder you come to on the right.  It has a small dead tree right next to the prominent arete.
